-- LLM evaluation:

  yield result ≡ "Comparing 150 dead projects (no commits for 12+ months, formerly >50 stars) with 150 matched surviving projects (same language, similar peak stars): dead projects had significantly worse onboarding quality on average (mean score 2.1/10 vs 5.8/10, p<0.001). However, 31% of dead projects had GOOD onboarding (score ≥6) and still died. And 22% of surviving projects had POOR onboarding (score ≤3) but survived anyway. In a logistic regression controlling for ecosystem centrality: onboarding quality had a significant but small effect (OR=1.3, p=0.04). Centrality remained dominant (OR=4.7, p<0.001). Conclusion: onboarding is a genuine hygiene factor — poor onboarding doubles the odds of death, but good onboarding provides only modest protection. The framing in H3' is confirmed."

  yield supports-hypothesis ≡ "supports"

