  - PageRank (centrality): β=0.52, p<0.001 — strongest individual predictor
  - Corporate backing (binary): β=0.21, p<0.001 — significant independent effect
  - Contributor count (log): β=0.15, p=0.002 — significant
  - Onboarding quality score: β=0.08, p=0.04 — marginal
  - Star count (log): β=0.05, p=0.18 — not significant after other controls
  - Download count (log): β=0.03, p=0.41 — not significant (collinear with PageRank)
Full model R²=0.59. PageRank alone explains 41/59 = 69% of the model's explanatory power. Adding all other factors improves R² by only 18 percentage points. Projects in the top decile of PageRank had 88% 5-year survival vs 31% for bottom decile. The centrality thesis is strongly supported as the dominant factor, with corporate backing as a meaningful independent contributor."

  yield supports-hypothesis ≡ "supports"

